The paper focuses on the development of online communities and the promotion of social interaction, which falls under the categories of social computing (cs.SOC) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of data from websites like Pinterest and Last.fm suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of social bootstrapping, which is a common technique in social networks and could be classified under social computing (cs.SOC) or information retrieval (cs.IR).
